sqlExprObj.sql: ((fatal_injury_rate BETWEEN 0 AND 15) AND (fatal_injury_crashes BETWEEN 0 AND 160) AND (non_motorized_fatal_injury BETWEEN 0 AND 5) AND (level_of_safety_service_kabc LIKE '%LOSS I%') OR (level_of_safety_service_kabc LIKE '%LOSS II%') OR (level_of_safety_service_kabc LIKE '%LOSS III%') OR (level_of_safety_service_kabc LIKE '%LOSS IV%') AND (excess_expected_kabc_crashes BETWEEN -50 AND 50))
sqlExprObj.displaySQL: (Rate of Fatalities and Injury related crashes per million entering vehicles is between 0 and 15) and (Number of Fatalities and Injury related crashes is between 0 and 160) and (Number of Non-motorized Fatality and Injury crashes is between 0 and 5) and (Level of Safety Service for KABC crashes using EB Method contains ('LOSS I','LOSS II','LOSS III','LOSS IV')) and (Difference between Expected Crashes and Predicted Crashes is between -50 and 50)

sqlExprObj.sql: ((fatal_injury_crashes BETWEEN 0 AND 1144) AND (fatal_injury_rate BETWEEN 0 AND 300) AND (excess_expected_kabc_crashes BETWEEN -180 AND 180))
sqlExprObj.displaySQL: (Number of Fatalities and Injury crashes is between 0 and 1144) and (Rate of Fatalities and Injury related crashes per million VMT is between 0 and 300) and (Level of Safety Service for KABC crashes using EB Method contains ?) and (Difference between Expected Crashes and Predicted Crashes is between -180 and 180)

sqlExprObj.sql: ((lowest_rating BETWEEN 1 AND 9) AND (type = 'Bridge') AND (deck_geometry_eval_068 BETWEEN 1 AND 9))
sqlExprObj.displaySQL: (Lowest Rating is between 1 and 9) and (Structure Type = 'Bridge') and (Deck Geometry Evaluation Rating is between 1 and 9)
(Average Daily Ridership is between 0 and 25000) and (Operator contains ?) and (Service Type contains ?)

sqlExprObj.sql: ((volume_2019 BETWEEN 0 AND 182500) AND (volume_2050 BETWEEN 0 AND 220000) AND (vc_2019 BETWEEN 0 AND 2.5) AND (vc_2050 BETWEEN 0 AND 3))

(Peak Period LOTTR is between 0 and 6) and (Daily Delay (Minutes) is between 0 and 500)
(Percent Disadvantaged Users is between 0 and 1) and (Trips by Disadvantaged Users is between 0 and 105000)

sqlExprObj.sql: ((hh_no_broadband BETWEEN 0 AND 458) AND (download_fixed BETWEEN 0 AND 1000) AND (download_mobile BETWEEN 0 AND 1000))

(Total population is between 0 and 14500) and (Transportation Factor (Definition N) = Yes)

config.text: Welcome to the Sun Cloud Explorer

Use this tool to explore data describing the Sun Corridor megaregion.


The side panel includes three interactive widgets - Layer Filters, Layer Visualization, and Project Weighting. Use the dots along the bottom of the panel to switch between widgets. Each widget includes an informational button for more details on using the widget.


The map includes widgets to zoom, search, and select features. Turn data layers on and off using the blue Map Layers widget. View data in a tabular format or export a data layer using the blue Table widget.

config.text: The Sun Cloud Explorer

The Sun Cloud Explorer serves as the gateway to access the Sun Cloud Portal data and tools. The Explorer provides an interactive and user-friendly experience to access high-quality transportation planning data layers and tools for the Sun Corridor region.


The Sun Cloud Explorer interface primarily includes a Map pane to the right and a Table of Contents pane on the left. The TOC pane includes three tabs


  1. Layers: Layers tab provides access to the Sun Cloud data layers that can be display one layer at a time or multiple layers at a time.
  2. Filters: Filters tab allows the users to further customize the data displayed in the map pane using predefined jurisdictional boundaries or data attributes.
  3. Scoring : The scoring tab includes unique tools that allows the users to perform needs assessment of infrastructure, generate performance metrics, and prioritize needs using a customizable set of scoring criteria. The scoring tab also includes a Needs Dashboard.

config.text: Additional Sun Cloud Explorer Resources

A full length Sun Cloud training was recorded in June of 2023. This recording, as well as additional information about the FHWA AID grant that helped fund the creation of the Sun Cloud, can be accessed from the MAG Performance Management site for the Sun Cloud.


Additional regional GIS data, viewers, and resources can be accessed on the Sun Cloud data portal Resources Page.


The Sun Cloud Explorer and data processing scripts used to produce the Sun Cloud layers are available in open source format from the project source code repository.
